{"TopicId":177695,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"How to change research limit amounts for career","CreatedByName":"devblazer","CreatedById":191366,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T15:14:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"devblazer","CreatedById":191366,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T15:14:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would like to change the max research amount in career mode for the 2nd upgrade of the research facility from 500 to 600.\u00A0 This would add a nice bit of balancing to my current career game and mods configuration.\u00A0 Is there anyway to do this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T15:27:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/191366-devblazer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022191366\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/191366-devblazer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@devblazer\u003C/a\u003E! Welcome to the forum. I put your post here in Technical Support. I think you\u0027ll get the most relevant help here. Have fun!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T16:41:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess, this can be done with a combination of \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/109027-14-custom-barn-kit-1117-march-10th-parachute-included/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ECustom Barn Kit\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/50533-141-module-manager-307-may-5th-2018-its-dangerous-to-go-alone-take-those-cats-with-you/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EModuleManager\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstall both mods (\u003Cs\u003Edon\u0027t forget to install the stock config file for the Custom Barn Kit as well, it is linked in the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP \u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/s\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EApparently, the default config is bundeld with the mod\u003C/abbr\u003E) and create a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch which contains:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\n@CUSTOMBARNKIT\n{\n\t@RESEARCH\n\t{\n\t\t@scienceCostLimit = 100, 600, -1\n\t}\n}\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EI haven\u0027t tested it but it should work \u003C/s\u003ETested and it works like a charm\u003Cs\u003E \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOfc, you can just edit the stock config of Custom Barn Kit instead of writing a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch but this is \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003Enot recommend.\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-08-20T17:30:33Z\u0022 title=\u002208/20/2018 05:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 20, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by 4x4cheesecake\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T17:00:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not totally sure about this, but it feels to me like this should be possible to do without installing a mod. Isn\u0027t there a simple file that can be edited somewhere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"4x4cheesecake","CreatedById":187982,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-20T17:21:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223437094\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022177695\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221534784429\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not totally sure about this, but it feels to me\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E like this should be possible to do without installing a mod\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E. Isn\u0027t there a simple file that can be edited somewhere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I\u0027m not sure either but I cannot find any file which contains these values and it feels to me that there is a reason for sarbian to write this mod. It seems to be an easy solution and there are mods mentioned in the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E, so I assume that using mods for this should be fine \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}